result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy D Frost was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal) - 2nd Offense, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 2:18 p.m. Defendant Timothy D Frost in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: NC. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Statement by the DE. Court orders: Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.
No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.    Complete ID process with the Sheriff's Department.

Case Called @ 3:13 PM: Defendant Timothy D Frost in court, appearing pro se.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  DA serves a copy of Complaint on Def - Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def produces proof of valid Class D DL for State's review.  State reviews same.  Off Record for validation to be performed.  Back of Record @ 3:24 PM:  State was able to determine that the status of the DL will need to be determined.  Abstract (27) is showing his DL is currently suspended.  Further investigation will be required.  NGP entered by the Court.   Def warned regarding driving status - and that he cannot drive legally.  STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for February 1, 2016 at 02:15 pm.
From Defendant requesting adjournment of INIT.
